\par Method developed for the chromatograph to analyze gas samples includes many parameters of the process, such as the specific task tim
e sequences, temperatures in working zones, names and chromatographic parameters of the gas or liquid to be analyzed, calibration standards, alarm levels for different components, types of detectors installed, parameters of the data acquisition, processin
g, analyzing, and outputting the results to other electronic equipment. 
\par    The Method for a particular application is set up through several }{\b\insrsid7345968 Method Menu}{\insrsid7345968  items:
\par }{\b\insrsid7345968 Method|Edit}{\insrsid7345968  item opens the }{\uldb\insrsid7345968 Method Dialog Box}{\v\insrsid7345968 ID_METHODDIALOG}{\insrsid7345968 
 to set the time schedule of the GC operations, Oven and Detector temperatures, points to be analyzed and to enable/disable alarms in those points. 
\par }{\b\insrsid7345968 Method|Detector}{\insrsid7345968  item opens the }{\uldb\insrsid7345968 Detector Dialog Box}{\v\insrsid7345968 ID_DETECTORDIALOG}{\insrsid7345968  so the user can enable/disable the part
icular detector, select the detector type, select the data acquisition parameters and the peak detection algorithm, and set the 4-20 mA analog output range.
\par }{\b\insrsid7345968 Method|Components}{\insrsid7345968  item opens the }{\uldb\insrsid7345968 Components Dialog Box}{\v\insrsid7345968 ID_COMPONENTSDIALOG}{\insrsid7345968  where the user can input 
the names, retention times, and other chromatographic parameters of the gas or liquid to be analyzed.
\par }{\b\insrsid7345968 Method|Standards}{\insrsid7345968  item opens the }{\uldb\insrsid7345968 Standards Dialog Box}{\v\uldb\insrsid7345968 ID_STANDARDSDIALOG}{\insrsid7345968 
 where the user inputs the concentration of the Standards (up to four) to be used for calibrating the instrument. 
\par }{\b\insrsid7345968 Method|Save}{\insrsid7345968 
 item saves all the parameters into the opened JOB file. It is possible to save different Methods into several JOB files; on start of the WPEAK program, the particular Method can be loaded automatically if one plac
es the corresponding JOB file name into the \'93Load File\'94 edit box in the }{\uldb\insrsid7345968 Preferences Dialog Box}{\v\insrsid7345968 ID_PREFERENCESDIALOG}{\insrsid7345968  that can be opened with the }{\b\insrsid7345968 Options|Preferences}{
\insrsid7345968  menu item.       
